---
import ServiceCityPage from '~/components/pages/ServiceCityPage.astro';
import { services, cities } from '~/data/service-city-config';
---

<ServiceCityPage service={services['panel-upgrades']} city={cities['holland-mi']}>
  <section class="container section-pad">
    <h2>Holland BPW $1,000 Panel Rebate</h2>
    <p>
      Holland Board of Public Works (BPW) offers a <strong>$1,000 rebate</strong> for residential panel upgrades to a minimum
      200-amp service when paired with an EV charger or a qualifying electric appliance installed within 12 months. If you
      live in the BPW electric service area and are upgrading your panel anyway, this rebate substantially offsets the project
      cost.
    </p>
    <p><strong>To qualify, you need:</strong></p>
    <ul>
      <li>Holland BPW as your electric provider (check your utility bill).</li>
      <li>A panel upgrade to at least 200 amps (from 100, 125, or 150 amp service).</li>
      <li>
        An EV charger <em>or</em> a 240V electric appliance (electric range, dryer, water heater, heat pump, induction cooktop)
        installed within 12 months of the panel upgrade.
      </li>
      <li>Licensed electrician with a closed electrical permit.</li>
      <li>Pre-approval recommended — call BPW at 616-355-1577 before starting.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      We handle the permit, the panel install, the EV charger (if you're bundling), and we provide the documentation
      packet you need for the BPW application. See our <a href="/blog/holland-bpw-panel-rebate-guide"
        >full Holland BPW rebate guide</a
      > for the step-by-step process and what stacks with federal and manufacturer incentives.
    </p>
  </section>
</ServiceCityPage>
